<TITLE> Delegates gather for South Africa ANC leadership vote </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Polokwane, South Africa, Dec 18 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - African National Congress delegates gathered on Tuesday for a leadership vote that could end President Thabo Mbeki's control over South Africa's ruling party and tilt the government to the left. The vote had originally been scheduled to start at 0400 GMT after two days of wrangling. If Mbeki's rival Jacob Zuma wins, he is almost certain to become president of South Africa when Mbeki has to stand down in 2009
